verbose_text: Similarly, as described above, in the T-bet and GATA-3-encoding plasmid injected fish, the expression of T-bet and GATA-3 in the muscle was significantly higher (p < 0.01) at all time points post-injection (day 2 and 7) and on day 4 post-challenge compared to fish that received the control plasmid, albeit with gradually decreasing levels of expression over time (XREF_FIG A, B).
